Package org.neo4j.internal.batchimport

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AdditionalInitialIds
    Migrating a store uses the ParallelBatchImporter to do so, where node/relationship stores are created with data read from legacy node/relationship stores.
    BatchImporter
    Imports graph data given as Input.
    Configuration
    Configuration for a an importer, mostly how and how much resources are used.
    GeneratingInputIterator.Generator<CHUNKSTATE>  
    ImportLogic.Monitor  
    InputIterable
    Iterable that returns InputIterator instances.
    InputIterator
    A ResourceIterator with added methods suitable for Input into a BatchImporter.
    Parallelizable
    Represents something that can be parallelizable, in this case that means the ability to dynamically change the number of processors executing tasks.
    PropertyValueLookup  
    RecordIdIterator
    Returns ids either backwards or forwards.
    RecordProcessor<T extends AbstractBaseRecord>
    Generic processor of AbstractBaseRecord from a store.
    RelationshipGroupDefragmenter.Monitor  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BatchImporterFactory  
    BatchingIdGetter
    Exposes batches of ids from a RecordStore as a LongIterator.
    CacheGroupsStep
    Caches RelationshipGroupRecord into RelationshipGroupCache.
    CalculateDenseNodesStep
    Increments counts for each visited relationship, once for start node and once for end node (unless for loops).
    Configuration.Overridden  
    CountGroupsStage
    Stage for counting groups per node, populates RelationshipGroupCache.
    CountGroupsStep
    After this step is ProcessorStep.done() all BOTH ID fields in the rel group cache will contain, for each node, the absolute number of groups from node 0 up to this point there is.
    DataImporter
    Imports data from Input into a store.
    DataImporter.ControllableStep
    Here simply to be able to fit into the ExecutionMonitor thing
    DataImporter.Monitor  
    DataStatistics
    Keeps data about how relationships are distributed between different types.
    DataStatistics.RelationshipTypeCount  
    DeleteDuplicateNodesStage
    After IdMapper.prepare(PropertyValueLookup, Collector, ProgressListener) any duplicate input ids have been detected, i.e. also duplicate imported nodes.
    DeleteDuplicateNodesStep  
    EncodeGroupsStep
    Takes cached relationship groups and sets real ids and next pointers, making them ready for writing to store.
    EntityImporter
    Abstract class containing logic for importing properties for an entity (node/relationship).
    ExhaustingEntityImporterRunnable
    Allocates its own InputChunk and loops, getting input data, importing input data into store until no more chunks are available.
    GeneratingInputIterator<CHUNKSTATE>
    A utility to be able to write an InputIterator with low effort.
    HeapSizeSanityChecker
    Sanity checking of Input.Estimates against heap size and free memory.
    HighestId
    Tracks a highest id when there are potentially multiple concurrent threads calling HighestId.offer(long).
    IdMapperPreparationStage
    Performs IdMapper.prepare(PropertyValueLookup, Collector, ProgressListener) embedded in a Stage as to take advantage of statistics and monitoring provided by that framework.
    IdMapperPreparationStep
    Preparation of an IdMapper, IdMapper.prepare(PropertyValueLookup, Collector, ProgressListener) under running as a normal Step so that normal execution monitoring can be applied.
    ImportLogic
    Contains all algorithms and logic for doing an import.
    ImportMemoryCalculator
    Aims to collect logic for calculating memory usage, optimal heap size and more, mostly based on Input.Estimates.
    IoThroughputStat
    Stat that provides a simple Mb/s stat, mostly used for getting an insight into I/O throughput.
    LabelIndexWriterStep  
    MemoryUsageStatsProvider
    Provides statistics about memory usage, as the key Keys.memory_usage
    NodeCountsAndLabelIndexBuildStage
    Counts nodes and their labels and also builds label index while doing so.
    NodeCountsProcessor
    Calculates counts per label and puts data into NodeLabelsCache for use by RelationshipCountsProcessor.
    NodeCountsStage
    Reads all records from NodeStore and process the counts in them, populating NodeLabelsCache for later use of RelationshipCountsStage.
    NodeDegreeCountStage
    Goes through RelationshipStore and increments counts per start/end node, calling NodeRelationshipCache.incrementCount(long).
    NodeFirstGroupStage
    Updates dense nodes with which will be the first group to point to, after a RelationshipGroupDefragmenter has been run.
    NodeImporter
    Imports nodes using data from InputChunk.
    NodeInputIdPropertyLookup
    Looks up "input id" from a node.
    NodeSetFirstGroupStep
    Scans group records and discovers which should affect the owners.
    ParallelBatchImporter
    BatchImporter which tries to exercise as much of the available resources to gain performance.
    ProcessRelationshipCountsDataStep
    Processes relationship records, feeding them to RelationshipCountsProcessor which keeps the accumulated counts per thread.
    RandomsStates
    Utility for generating deterministically randomized data, even though chunks may be reordered during actual import.
    ReadGroupRecordsByCacheStep
    Using the NodeRelationshipCache efficiently looks for changed nodes and reads those NodeRecord and sends downwards.
    ReadGroupsFromCacheStep
    Reads group records from RelationshipGroupCache, sending them downstream in batches.
    ReadNodeIdsByCacheStep
    Using the NodeRelationshipCache efficiently looks for changed nodes and reads those NodeRecord and sends downwards.
    RecordIdIterator.Backwards  
    RecordIdIterator.Forwards  
    RecordProcessorStep<T extends AbstractBaseRecord>
    RecordProcessor in Step-form.
    RelationshipCountsAndTypeIndexBuildStage
    Reads all records from RelationshipStore and process the counts in them.
    RelationshipCountsProcessor
    Calculates counts as labelId --[type]--> labelId for relationships with the labels coming from its start/end nodes.
    RelationshipCountsStage
    Reads all records from RelationshipStore and process the counts in them.
    RelationshipGroupCache
    Holds information vital for making RelationshipGroupDefragmenter work the way it does.
    RelationshipGroupDefragmenter
    Defragments RelationshipGroupRecord so that they end up sequential per node in the group store.
    RelationshipGroupStage
    Takes information about relationship groups in the NodeRelationshipCache, which is produced as a side-effect of linking relationships together, and writes them out into RelationshipGroupStore.
    RelationshipImporter
    Imports relationships using data from InputChunk.
    RelationshipLinkbackStage
    Sets RelationshipRecord.setFirstPrevRel(long) and RelationshipRecord.setSecondPrevRel(long) by going through the RelationshipStore in reversed order.
    RelationshipLinkbackStep
    Links relationship chains together, the "prev" pointers of them.
    RelationshipLinkforwardStage  
    RelationshipLinkforwardStep  
    RelationshipLinkingProgress
    Able to provide Keys.progress.
    RelationshipLinkStep
    Links relationship chains together, the "prev" pointers of them.
    RelationshipTypeIndexWriterStep  
    ScanAndCacheGroupsStage
    Scans RelationshipGroupRecord from store in reverse, this because during import the relationships are imported per type in descending type id order, i.e. with highest type first.
    SparseNodeFirstRelationshipProcessor
    Sets the relationship field on sparse nodes.
    SparseNodeFirstRelationshipStage
    Updates sparse node records with relationship heads after relationship linking.
    StandardBatchImporterFactory  
    UpdateRecordsStep<RECORD extends AbstractBaseRecord>
    Updates a batch of records to a store.
    Utils
    Common and cross-concern utilities.
    WriteGroupsStage
    Writes cached RelationshipGroupRecord from ScanAndCacheGroupsStage to store.
